 Police operatives of the Gender Unit of the Federal Capital Territory (FCT), Abuja, Police Command have arrested a 43-year-old man for raping his 15-year old daughter. Also the police arrested a 20-year-old boy for raping a six-year-old boy. Addressing reporters in Abuja yesterday, the Commissioner of Police, Bala Ciroma, said the suspects confessed to the crimes. “On 15th April, 2020 police operatives from the Command Gender Unit arrested one Akindele Ajewole ‘m’ 43years at Lugbe for defiling his 15-year old daughter.  The mentally stable suspect confessed to have had carnal knowledge of his daughter on many occasions. “In another development, on 5th April, 2020 police operatives from Mpape arrested one Mohammed Sani ‘m’ 20 years for luring and forcefully having carnal knowledge with a six- year-old boy. The suspect stated that he committed the unnatural act with the minor while they were swimming at a river in Mpape. “The suspects will be arraigned in court upon the conclusion of investigation,” he said.